Put a large #saucepan{} of water with @salt{0.5%tsp} on to boil for the pasta. Halve, peel and thinly slice the @echalion shallot{1}. Peel and grate the @garlic{2%cloves}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}). Pull a #vegetable peeler{} lengthways along the @courgette{1} to make ribbons (see picture). Finely chop the @chives{1}(finely chopped) (use scissors if you want). Zest and halve the @lemon{1/2}(zested and halved).

Add the @rigatoni pasta{200%g} to the pan of boiling water and simmer until cooked, ~{12%minutes}. When ready, reserve some of the pasta cooking water, then drain in a #colander{}, return to the pan and drizzle over some oil to stop it sticking together.

Meanwhile, heat a glug of oil in a #frying pan{} on medium heat. Once hot, add the @rainbow chard{150%g}. Season with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{} and stir-fry until starting to soften, ~{3-4%minutes}. Add the @courgette ribbons{} and garlic, mix well and cook for ~{2-3%minutes} more. Pop the greens in a #mixing bowl{} and cover with some foil to keep warm.

Put your frying pan back on medium heat with a splash of @oil{} and add the @vivera plant chicken pieces{175%g}. Stir fry until golden on the outside, ~{4-5%minutes}.

> MOD: If you've added veggie Vivera plant 'chicken' to your meal, before adding the shallot to the pan, add the veggie 'chicken' and stir until golden on the outside, 4-5 mins. Add the shallot to the pan with the 'chicken' and continue with the recipe as instructed.

Then add the shallot and stir together. Cook until the shallot has softened, stirring occasionally, ~{4-5%minutes}, then add the @vegetable stock powder{1%tsp} and @reserved pasta water{100%ml}. Stir to dissolve the stock powder, then simmer until reduced by half, ~{3-4%minutes}. Stir in the @creme fraiche{150%g}, heat through until piping hot, then season with @ground black pepper{}. Stir through the chives and three quarters of the @grated hard Italian style cheese{40%g}.

Add the pasta to your sauce along with half the greens, stir everything together.

> Tip: If the sauce needs loosening up, just add a splash of water. If you feel the creamy sauce is a little bit thick, add a little bit of the starchy pasta water to loosen up the consistency. The salty, starchy water not only adds flavor but helps the sauce cling to the rigatoni.

Add a pinch of lemon zest and a squeeze of lemon juice. Taste and add more lemon juice, salt and pepper if you like things zingy!

Serve the creamy pasta in #bowls{} with the remaining greens on top and a sprinkling of the remaining hard Italian cheese. Enjoy!